 lower the term 
\begin_inset Formula $(\frac{y_{2}-y_{1}}{2\delta})^{1/3}$
\end_inset

.
 In other words, the impatience for investment (or consumption) in the current
 period (rather than the next) may rise to satisfy the population constraint.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A more stringent requirement from the population constraint could be that
 
\begin_inset Formula $\rho(t)$
\end_inset

